
[1]insulate

   IN'SULATE, v.t. [L. insula, an isle.] To place in a detached situation,
   or in a state to have no communication with surrounding objects.

   1. In architecture, to set a column alone or not contiguous to a wall.

   2. In electrical experiments, to place on a non-conducting substance,
   or in a situation to prevent communication with the earth.

   3. To make an isle. [Little used.]
